{
  "texts": [
    "Gramopadhye et al. (2024) further demonstrated that providing in-context examples can enhance the quality of the CoT reasoning.",
    "Building on these approaches, Wang et al. (2023) proposed the Self-Consistency method, which generates multiple reasoning paths through sampling and selects the most consistent answer across those paths.",
    "Similarly, Yao et al. (2023) introduced Tree-of-Thought (ToT) reasoning, where each reasoning step branches into multiple possibilities, forming a tree structure.",
    "The final answer is selected from the most consistent outcome at the leaves of the tree.",
    "Following ToT, Zhou et al. (2023) introduced the Least-to-Most prompting method that breaks complex problems into smaller sub-problems, which the LLM solves sequentially using CoT reasoning."
  ]
}